{
  "stem": "2966.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "I had no way-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there was no way how to-- to survive.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "While in that camp, I must tell you that, in April of 1944, there was one transport of people from that camp taken away to a concentration camp near Cracow, which was called Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "I'll spell it to you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "It's P-L-A-S-Z-O-W.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That was right on the outskirts of Cracow.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And a transport from our work camp was taken there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But the Germans, for whatever reason, and also the chief of our Jewish police at that time, was taken away to that Plaszow concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "A few months later, the Germans brought him back from that concentration camp to show to the rest of the Jews proof that they're not being killed.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "They're only take-- being taken to work in a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And truthfully, he did come with them to tell people that people weren't killed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "They were taken to a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] He also knew, at that time, who was hiding in the forest and who was not.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "He had his information.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "And when that German SS man brought me in, he knew I wasn't hiding in the forest.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "Because if you were hiding in the forest, they used to beat you till you tell them where the people were hidden.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "And if you didn't tell them, they killed you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Somebody must have pointed me out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the only way, till today, that I can explain.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because it was in a part of town that I don't think anybody knew me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But you never know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Somebody must have passed by and pointed me out to him, because I lived later as a Pole, and no-- between Polacks.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
